The paper deals with anti-money laundering in the context of Bitcoin transactions, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically graph convolutional networks, for financial forensics, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the use of data visualization and analysis, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a large dataset and data management techniques, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the societal impact of financial exclusion and inclusion, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
